events.message: Remove unused bits from the service flags enum

events.body:
I'm still seeing nodes on the network advertising the THIN service bit, e.g.:-

> 2020-04-04 18:50:59.012  recv version: /Classic:1.3.4(EB8)/: version 80002, blocks=642087, relay=1, services=0x35 us=x.x.x.x:8333, them=103.76.41.69:57664, peer=42933
> 2020-04-09 06:28:14.209  recv version: /BUCash:1.1.2(EB16; AD12)/: version 80003, blocks=530361, relay=1, services=0x35 us=x.x.x.x:8333, them=31.172.81.167:43308, peer=364

I am seeing fewer nodes using GETUTXO than are using XTHIN so it would have made more sense to remove that service bit.
